Manufacturer Usage Description (MUD) for
TLS and DTLS Profiles for Internet of
Things (IoT) Devices
2025", shape=ellipse, URL="RFC9761.html", target="_top", tooltip="This memo extends the Manufacturer Usage Description (MUD) specification to allow manufacturers to define TLS and DTLS profile parameters.  This allows a network security service to identify unexpected (D)TLS usage, which can indicate the presence of unauthorized software, malware, or security policy-violating traffic on an endpoint."];
  RFC9761 -> rev_cites;
  RFC9872 [label="RFC9872
Recommendations for Discovering IPv6
Prefix Used for IPv6 Address Synthesis
2025", shape=ellipse, URL="RFC9872.html", target="_top", tooltip="On networks providing IPv4-IPv6 translation (RFC 7915), hosts and other endpoints need to know the IPv6 prefix(es) used for translation (the NAT64 prefix (RFC 6052)).  This document provides guidelines for NAT64 prefix discovery, specifically recommending obtaining the NAT64 prefix from the Router Advertisement option (RFC 8781) when available."];
